{#-
  ButtonGroup — container that sticks N Buttons together with collapsed
  adjacent borders. Visual: a single "segmented" pill where each cell
  is a real <button> (or <a>) with its own focus + click semantics.

  Zero Stimulus controller. ButtonGroup is NOT a roving-tabindex pattern
  (contrast with ToggleGroup) — each inner Button keeps its own Tab stop
  because each fires a distinct action. The group is purely visual +
  semantic (role="group" + aria-label).

  Two usage patterns:

  1. {% embed %} — the canonical Twig way, lets the consumer pass the
     inner buttons via the `buttons` block:

       {% embed '@cremona/components/button-group/button-group.html.twig' with {
         label: 'Actions du fichier'|trans, size: 'md',
       } %}
         {% block buttons %}
           {% include '@cremona/components/button/button.html.twig' with { label: 'Save'|trans } %}
           {% include '@cremona/components/button/button.html.twig' with { label: 'Cancel'|trans, variant: 'secondary' } %}
         {% endblock %}
       {% endembed %}

  2. Raw HTML — the CSS contract works on any `<button class="cremona-button">`
     placed inside `<div class="cremona-button-group" role="group">`:

       <div class="cremona-button-group" role="group" aria-label="...">
         <button class="cremona-button" data-variant="primary" ...>Save</button>
         <button class="cremona-button" data-variant="secondary" ...>Cancel</button>
       </div>

  Parameters:
    label         (string, required) — aria-label for the group (every group MUST have an
                                       accessible name; axe `aria-allowed-attr` + screen-reader UX).
                                       Use `labelledById` instead if the label lives in another
                                       element (a visible heading) that the group references.
    labelledById  (string, optional) — id of an existing element that names the group;
                                       overrides `label` when set.
    orientation   (string, optional) — horizontal (default) | vertical
    attached      (bool,   optional) — true (default) → collapsed adjacent borders, segmented look.
                                       false → keep each Button standalone with a spacing gap.
    size          (string, optional) — informational (not propagated automatically);
                                       consumers pass `size` to each inner Button themselves.
    className     (string, optional)

  Block `buttons` (required when embedding):
    N <button> or <a> elements with `class="cremona-button"`. The CSS handles
    border-radius collapsing + adjacent border removal — no extra attributes
    are needed on the inner buttons themselves.
-#}

{%- set label        = label        | default(null) -%}
{%- set labelledById = labelledById | default(null) -%}
{%- set orientation  = orientation  | default('horizontal') -%}
{%- set attached     = attached is defined ? attached : true -%}
{%- set size         = size         | default(null) -%}
{%- set className    = className    | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-button-group'] -%}
{%- if not attached -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge(['cremona-button-group--detached']) -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  role="group"
  data-orientation="{{ orientation }}"
  {%- if size %} data-size="{{ size }}"{% endif -%}
  {%- if labelledById %} aria-labelledby="{{ labelledById }}"
  {%- elseif label %} aria-label="{{ label }}"{% endif -%}
>
  {%- block buttons -%}{%- endblock -%}
</div>
